<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Regulation FD Disclosure. </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On March&nbsp;27, 2009, Kraft Foods Inc.
issued a press release announcing that Tim McLevish, Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer, would be meeting with analysts in New York City on Friday, March&nbsp;27, 2009. The meeting is solely to discuss Kraft Foods&#146; revised
presentation of financial results from prior periods, coinciding with previously announced changes in the company&#146;s operating structure and other accounting changes, primarily a change from the use of the LIFO inventory method for some domestic
inventories to the average cost method. Copies of the slides used in the discussion and a copy of the press release are attached as Exhibit 99.1 and Exhibit 99.2 and are incorporated by reference into this Item&nbsp;7.01. </FONT></P> <P
STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

Foods</div> <div style='position:absolute;left:472px;top:406px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:43px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Review of Changes to </div> <div

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" COLOR="#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
  <div STYLE="position: relative; left: auto; top: auto;">
<table id="pageTable" width="981" height="742">
<tr>
<td nowrap> <div style='position:absolute;left:10px;top:10px'>
<img src="g35157ex99_1s2gbgd.jpg" width="961" height="689" border="0" alt=""></div> <div style='position:absolute;left:953px;top:711px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#808080;'>2</div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:34px;top:40px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:36px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#FFFFFF;'>Forward&#45;looking statements</div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:163px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>This slide presentation contains forward&#45;looking statements that there are two critical aspects
of Kraft Foods' financial turnaround, </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:180px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>including returning to sustainable growth and
improving transparency, accountability and decision&#45;making; the five ways we're </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:196px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>improving transparency, accountability and decision&#45;making, in particular, that we are
reorganizing European operations for faster </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:212px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>decision&#45;making and for better
trade&#45;offs, revising cost assignment methodology and moving to LIFO to reduce accounting costs; our </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:228px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>U.S. beverages key initiatives, including that we will invest in value&#45;oriented marketing,
increase top&#45;line momentum of powdered </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:244px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>beverage stick and premium coffee platforms
and improve profitability of ready&#45;to&#45;drink and mainstream coffee; our U.S. cheese key </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:261px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>initiatives, including that we will apply an adaptive pricing model for more consistent profit
delivery, enhance product mix through </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:277px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>incremental marketing behind advantaged
categories and segments, and that we will leverage our scale to create retail advantage; </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:293px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>our U.S. convenient meals key initiatives, including our focus on quality, marketing and innovation
around sandwiches, that we will </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:309px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>sustain top&#45;line momentum of pizza, and grow our
margins through &#34;end to end&#34; productivity opportunities; our Grocery initiatives, </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:325px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>including focusing our resources on fewer, bigger core platforms, leverage in&#45;store presence
with better trade planning and execution </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:342px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>tools, and streamline overhead and
manufacturing through &#34;end&#45;to&#45;end&#34; initiatives; our U.S. snacks initiatives, including continuing to </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:358px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>revitalize core cookie and cracker brands by further investments and building margin&#45;accretive
platforms that leverage core equities, </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:374px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>grow share in nuts through quality upgrades and
participation in growing segments, selectively invest in bars, and invest to optimize </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:390px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>manufacturing infrastructure; our Canada and North American Foodservice key initiatives, including
growing vol/mix, leveraging scale, </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:406px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>optimizing our Canadian manufacturing network,
improving product mix by focusing on Kraft brands, and building profit margins by </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:423px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>leveraging growth in profitable customer segments; our Europe key initiatives, including focusing
where we make money, investing </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:439px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>behind the highest margin opportunities, pruning less
profitable product lines, improving effectiveness at retail, eliminating inefficient </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:455px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>trade spending, driving portfolio availability, reducing costs by streamlining overheads and
manufacturing, and integrating our Kraft </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:471px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Foods and LU businesses; our Developing
Markets key initiatives, including growing through locally relevant business models, </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:488px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>continuing to focus investments behind priority categories, brands and markets and expanding in
traditional trade channels; our 2009 </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:504px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>goal to build profit margins and market share; and
our long&#45;term goals with regard to organic revenue growth, manufacturing, </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:520px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>overhead
leverage, cash flow leverage, tax rate, and long&#45;term EPS growth. These forward&#45;looking statements involve risks and </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:536px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>uncertainties that could cause actual results to differ materially from those predicted in any such
forward&#45;looking statements. Such </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:552px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>factors, include, but are not limited to,
continued volatility of input costs, pricing actions, increased competition, our ability to </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:568px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>differentiate our products from private label products, increased costs of sales, FDA or other
regulatory actions or delays including </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:585px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>widespread product recalls, unanticipated
expenses such as litigation or legal settlement expenses, our indebtedness and ability to pay</div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:601px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>our indebtedness, the shift in our product mix to lower margin offerings, our failure to expand
into emerging markets, risks from </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:617px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>operating internationally and tax law changes. For
additional information on these and other factors that could affect our forward&#45;</div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:633px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>looking statements, see our filings with the SEC, including our most recently filed Annual Report
on Form 10&#45;K and subsequent reports</div> <div style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:649px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>on Forms 10&#45;Q and 8&#45;K. We disclaim and
do not undertake any obligation to update or revise any forward&#45;looking statement in this </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:37px;top:666px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:13px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>slide presentation.<font size='3.2' face='"times new roman","times new roman",times,serif'>
</font></div> </td></tr></table></div>

style='position:absolute;left:596px;top:415px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>2&#45;3pp</div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:192px;top:446px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Cash Flow Leverage &#38; Tax Rate&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:596px;top:446px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:19px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>1&#45;2pp</div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:192px;top:495px;font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;font-size:19px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>Long&#45;Term EPS Growth&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </div> <div
style='position:absolute;left:568px;top:495px;font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;font-size:19px;font-family:verdana,arial,sans-serif;color:#000000;'>7%&#45;9%</div> </td></tr></table></div>

<DESCRIPTION>KRAFT FOODS INC. PRESS RELEASE, DATED MARCH 27, 2009.

<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Kraft Foods Inc. Press Release, dated March 27, 2009.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exhibit 99.2 </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right">

<IMG SRC="g35157g06l57.jpg" ALT="LOGO"> </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" ALIGN="center">

<TR>

<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U>ir@kraft.com</U></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I></I><B>KRAFT FOODS MEETS WITH ANALYSTS TODAY</B><I> </I></FONT></P> <P
STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">NORTHFIELD, Ill. &#150; March&nbsp;27, 2009 &#150; Kraft Foods Inc. (NYSE: KFT) announced that Tim McLevish, Executive Vice President and CFO, will meet
today with analysts in New York City. The meeting is solely to discuss Kraft Foods&#146; revised presentation of financial results from prior periods, coinciding with previously announced changes in the company&#146;s operating structure and other
accounting changes, primarily a change from the use of the LIFO inventory method for some domestic inventories to the average cost method. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"
SIZE="2">On March&nbsp;26, 2009, Kraft Foods filed a Form 8-K with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) with financial schedules for 2008, 2007 and 2006 reflecting these changes. As disclosed in its Annual Report on Form 10-K for the
year ended Dec. 31, 2008, which was filed with the SEC on Feb. 27, 2009, Kraft Foods announced changes in its operating structure, effective January 2009. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Today, Kraft Foods also filed a Form 8-K with the SEC with the slides used in the discussion with analysts. These slides are available at <U>http://www.kraftfoodscompany.com</U> and <U>http://idea.sec.gov</U>.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods makes today delicious in 150 countries around the globe. Our 100,000 Kraft Foodies work tirelessly to make delicious foods
consumers can feel good about. From American brand icons like <I>Kraft</I> cheeses, dinners and dressings, <I>Maxwell House</I> coffees and <I>Oscar Mayer</I> meats, to global powerhouse brands like <I>Oreo</I> and <I>LU</I> biscuits,
<I>Philadelphia</I> cream cheeses, <I>Jacobs</I> and <I>Carte Noire</I> coffees, <I>Tang</I> powdered beverages and <I>Milka</I>, <I>C&ocirc;te d&#146;Or</I>, <I>Lacta</I> and <I>Toblerone</I> chocolates, our brands inspire millions of delicious
moments every day. Kraft Foods is the world&#146;s second largest food company with annual revenues of $42 billion. The company is a member of the Dow Jones Industrial Average, Standard&nbsp;&amp; Poor&#146;s 500, the Dow Jones Sustainability Index
and Ethibel Sustainability Index. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">#&nbsp;&nbsp;#&nbsp;&nbsp;# </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;
</FONT></P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE="2">1 </FONT></P>
